Wrote `error-handling-findings.md`. One MEDIUM finding (a verified silent-failure regression introduced by this PR), one LOW (pre-existing, deferred), one N/A (the unrelated models removal).

**Key result**: Empirically verified that with GitHub Actions' default `bash --noprofile --norc -eo pipefail`, `RESP=$(curl -sf ...)` on HTTP 4xx exits the script at the assignment line with curl exit 22 — so the carefully-crafted `"::error::RAILWAY_TOKEN is invalid or expired"` and "rotate the token" lines that follow are never reached. This contradicts the PR description's claim that "the jq guard catches all cases generically." The regression's real-world impact depends on whether Railway's GraphQL endpoint returns HTTP 200 (with errors body) or HTTP 4xx for invalid tokens — a question the PR did not answer or document. Recommended fix: revert the validate step to `curl -s` (Option A) or use explicit `|| RC=$?` capture (Option C). Verdict: NEEDS_DISCUSSION (PR already merged; findings are advisory).
